OL,3,CCross-border tourism has tripled in a
OL,4,Cdecade ` all-island report
OL,6,FCross-border tourism between Northern
OL,7,FIreland and the Republic of Ireland
OL,8,Fhas tripled in a decade, a report has
OL,9,Ffound.
OL,11,FThe joint study by Ulster University
OL,12,Fand Dublin City University found there
OL,13,Fwere differences in the economic
OL,14,Fimpact in Ireland compared with
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland.
OL,17,FThere were more than 1.3 million cross-
OL,18,Fborder visits made to Northern Ireland
OL,19,Fin 2023, compared with almost 400,000
OL,20,Fin 2013.
