OL,3,CCross-border tourism has tripled in a
OL,4,Cdecade ` all-island report
OL,6,F"In 2013, on average less than 100,000
OL,7,Fcross-border trips were made per
OL,8,Fquarter, a figure that has grown to
OL,9,Fover 300,000 in 2023. In the years
OL,10,Ffollowing the pandemic, over 200,000
OL,11,Ftrips per quarter have been recorded,"
OL,12,Fit said.
OL,14,FThe study found that all visitors to
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland are more likely to be
OL,16,Fvisiting friends or relatives than on
OL,17,Fholiday or a business trip, and of
OL,18,Fthat number almost half will stay with
OL,19,Fthem ` considerably reducing the
OL,20,Fearned income from accommodation.
