OL,3,CCross-border tourism has tripled in a
OL,4,Cdecade ` all-island report
OL,6,FVisitors from Great Britain are
OL,7,Fcrucial to both parts of the island,
OL,8,Fthe study found, but the scale is
OL,9,Fdifferent, making up two thirds of
OL,10,Fvisitors to Northern Ireland compared
OL,11,Fwith one third in Ireland.
OL,13,FThe report found people stay in
OL,14,FNorthern Ireland for fewer nights,
OL,15,Fparticularly long-haul visitors.
OL,17,FIt also found a "buoyant and
OL,18,Fresilient" tourism industry across
OL,19,Fboth Northern Ireland and Ireland,
OL,20,Fwith "strong evidence" of a bounce
OL,21,Fback from the Covid-19 pandemic.
