OL,3,CCross-border tourism has tripled in a
OL,4,Cdecade ` all-island report
OL,6,FIt said Ireland had approximately 4.3
OL,7,Ftimes as many trips by international
OL,8,Fvisitors compared with Northern
OL,9,FIreland in 2019, but 7.6 times as much
OL,10,Fexpenditure.
OL,12,FThe scale of domestic tourism trips
OL,13,Fwithin Northern Ireland, at roughly
OL,14,Ftwo million per annum, remained static
OL,15,Fin the decade from 2011.
OL,17,FSouth of the border, the scale of
OL,18,Fwithin-state tourism increased from
OL,19,F6.5 million to 11 million trips in the
OL,20,Fsame period, probably reflecting the
OL,21,Fstronger economic performance.
