OL,3,CCross-border tourism has tripled in a
OL,4,Cdecade ` all-island report
OL,6,F"Tourism growth and development is a
OL,7,Fnatural area for co-operation across
OL,8,Fthe island and has been ongoing for
OL,9,Fmany years. The sector has
OL,10,Fdemonstrated that it can adapt to
OL,11,Fexternal challenges and recover
OL,12,Fstrongly.
OL,14,F"It will need this quality to tackle
OL,15,Fthe current challenges which have been
OL,16,Fidentified by businesses both sides of
OL,17,Fthe border, which include labour
OL,18,Fmarket shortages and concerns over the
OL,19,Fcost of doing business."
