OL,3,CCross-border tourism has tripled in a
OL,4,Cdecade ` all-island report
OL,6,FProfessor John Doyle, vice president
OL,7,Ffor Research at Dublin City
OL,8,FUniversity, said the research
OL,9,F"highlights a real opportunity for
OL,10,Feconomic growth, for businesses to
OL,11,Fgrow their income and profitability,
OL,12,Fand for better wages in the sector".
OL,14,F"Co-operation will benefit both parts
OL,15,Fof the island, but given the more
OL,16,Fdeveloped tourism industry in the
OL,17,FRepublic, it should benefit Northern
OL,18,FIreland to a much greater extent.
